         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">St Petersburg, 20 July 1879 ¶ Revered friend, ¶  ¶ In reply to your letter of 5 May, ¶  which has just arrived, as follows: The remarks on  ¶ Elaeagnus kologa ¶  are by C. Salomon, ¶  who is hardly ve...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">79.08.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Eduard von Regel</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found bound into front of a copy of vol. 1 of Franchet &amp; Savatier (1875-9). The Julian calendar was used in Russia until 1917; 12 days need to be added to arrive at the Gregorian date that provides the basis for the numbering of the letter.</p>
               </note>St Petersburg den</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">20 Juli 79</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochgeehrter Freund!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In Erwiederung Ihres Schreibens vom 5/5 das mir so eben zugegangen, das Folgende: Die Bemerkungen über Elaeagnus Kologa sind von C. Salomon, der kaum in dieser Beziehung ganz sicher ist und nur nach De Candolle geht.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Die Elaeagnus hat C. Maximowicz in der 8ten Decade (pag. 558) seiner neuen Pflanzen Japans und der Mandschurei, welche Maximowicz Ihnen seiner Zeit auch gesendet hat.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Zu <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">E. latifolia L.</hi>
               </seg> zieht Maximowicz E. arborea Roxbrg, E. conferta Roxbrg, E. Thwaitesi Schlechtd., E. Kaloga Schlechtd., E. ferruginea Rich. u. E. Wallichiana Schlechtd..</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Zu <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">E. umbellata Thbg</hi>
               </seg> stellt er E. parvifolia <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Roxbrg</hi>
               </seg> als Synonym, - und von <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">E. longipes A. Gray</hi>
               </seg> (wozu Maximowicz E. crispa u. E. multiflora als Synonyme zieht), führt er eine Form als α <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hortensis</hi>
               </seg> mit grossen essbaren Früchten auf. Doch Sie werden ja diese kurze Abhandlung von Maximowicz selbst haben.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Indem ich Sie nun noch auf das herzlichste Grüsse, bin und bleibe ich Ihr ganz ergebener</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">College und Freund</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>E v Regel</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">St Petersburg, 20 July 1879</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Revered friend,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your letter of 5 May,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. </p>
               </note> which has just arrived, as follows: The remarks on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Elaeagnus%20kologa">Elaeagnus kologa</name>
               </seg> are by C. Salomon,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Regel was the editor of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gartenflora</seg>, in which, in vol. 28 (1879), p. 11, the notes on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. kologa</seg> appear in <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Bemerkungen über verschiedene ältere und neuere Freilandgehölze', pp. 10-16, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>signed "(C. S.)".</p>
               </note> who is hardly very reliable in this respect, as he just repeats De Candolle.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Elaeagnus</seg> was treated by C. Maximowicz in the 8th decade (page 558) of his new plants of Japan and Manchuria,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Maximowicz (1870a), pp. 558-61.</p>
               </note> which Maximowicz sent to you at the time.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">There is a reprint of Maximowicz's paper in the Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne, inscribed: 'Illo viro F. Müller auctor' [To F. Müller from the author].</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Maximowicz unites <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. arborea</seg> Roxb., <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. conferta</seg> Roxb., <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. thwaitesii</seg> Schlechtd., <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. kologa</seg> Schlechtd., <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. ferruginea</seg> Rich. and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. wallichiana</seg> Schlechtd. under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. latifolia</seg> L.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He places <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. parvifolia</seg> Roxb. as synonym under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. umbellata</seg> Thunb., and under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. longipes</seg> A. Gray (into which Maximowicz places <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. crispa</seg> and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. multiflora</seg> as synonyms) he lists a form as<seg style="font-style: italic; "> α</seg>
               <seg style="font-size: 12pt; font-style: italic; "> </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">hortensis</seg> with large edible fruit. But you will have this short paper by Maximowicz yourself.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With my most sincere regards I am and remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your most devoted colleague and friend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>E. von Regel.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
